    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.62.22" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        5835 Vine Street
                        Lincoln, Nebraska 68<del>9</del><add>5</add>05
                        April 9, 1971
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Dr. Bower Aly</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Department of Speech</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Oregon</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Eugene, Oregon 97403</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Bower:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Bless your heart and many thanks. I certainly do deeply appreciate what you have just done in the interest of the Dick Cavett show and my work generally. Your latest efforts are too characteristic for thanks and I feel almost guilty when I thank you again (nevertheless, please don't quit!). I note that the Dick Cavett address that you give is not quite correct. It should be American Broadcasting Company, 17<del>0</del><add>90</add> Broadway, New York, <hi rend="caps">N. Y.</hi> 10019.</p>
                
                <p>It does look as though there is a ground swell<sic>groundswell</sic> of interest in my stuff. It's a constant surprise to me.</p>
                
                <p>I have just signed an option contract with a movie producer.</p>
                
                <p>I do want to know more about Lucile's progress with the revision job. It's going to be a great day when we see that in print.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With the old affection,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>
                    
                    <note>JGN:nh</note>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
        
